2. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with finding a spanning tree in a graph, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of discrete structures such as graphs and trees, which is a topic in discrete mathematics.

5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper involves the use of numerical methods to approximate the properties of minimum spanning trees and shortest path trees.
